#: ../../remote_sensing.rst:721
msgid ""
"One of the main benefit of the :guilabel:`Land Cover Signature "
"Classification` is that it is possible to select pixels and and include the "
"signature thereof in a spectral range; therefore, the classification should "
"be the direct representation of the class expected for every spectral "
"signature. This is very suitable for the classification of a single land "
"cover class (defined by specific spectral thresholds), and leave "
"unclassified the rest of the image that is of no interest for the purpose of"
" the classification."
